    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to
                                Governor <persName type="to">Nicholls</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                1890</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Italian minister earnestly represents that, according to advices from
                            the Italian consul at New Orleans, the mayor of that city has caused the
                            arrest of innocent persons and issued proclamations tending to excite
                            the whole Italian colony. The minister is confident that the great body
                            of Italians in New Orleans repudiate with horror the act of a few
                            criminals, and have no other desire than to see the law take its course
                            and punish the murderers of the chief of police.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
